overview: The user initiated a request to assess their existing sleep
  questionnaire application against a provided Statement of Work. The primary
  goal was to integrate a database for storing questionnaire responses, develop
  an admin dashboard for data access, and implement a simple authentication
  mechanism. After an initial codebase evaluation, it was determined that while
  the questionnaire logic and PDF generation were in place, database storage,
  data retrieval (CSV export), and an admin dashboard with authentication were
  missing. I clarified with the user regarding the desired complexity of
  authentication (simple password via environment variable) and the specific
  demographic fields to be collected (combining existing and SOW-specified
  fields). Subsequently, a comprehensive plan was developed, detailing the
  necessary updates to the Prisma schema, creation of API routes for saving and
  retrieving responses, implementation of a lightweight authentication system,
  and the development of an admin dashboard with CSV export functionality. The
  plan was approved, and I began the implementation process.
